enterpriseBody: Created by Law 51-92 of May 18, 1992; ISET Radès is a Tunisian university institute attached to the university. The teaching is provided there for the most part by teachers from the body of technologists. Placed under the supervision of the Ministry of Higher Education and Scientific Research and managed by the general management; offer initial training leading to a diploma, continuing education linked to the needs of companies, a technological resource centre, a skills center and a business incubator.
nameBody:
Bitrate: 
In telecommunications and computing, bitrate is the number of bits that are conveyed or processed per unit of time. In plain English, it’s the speed in which your data, or video, flies across the Internet. If your bitrate is too slow it may result in a poor quality video which may lag or look distorted.

founderBody: Mariem Abdi -23 years old-, is a mobile application development Masters student in ISET Rades, Tunisia.
valuesBody:
Reliability: We aim to make users able to depend on the application for consistent performance and uninterrupted streaming.

Scalability and Performance: We aim to make a solution that can handle a large number of concurrent users and high-demand situations.

Customizability and Branding: We aim to provide our users with the ability to customize the application's user interface and branding to align with their corporate identity.

Security and Compliance: We make sure that all of our users' information are saved securely and safely.
